 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🐛 CoBug AI Learning Platform\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the full platform (React frontend + Node.js backend) directly in Google Colab using **ngrok** to expose it to the internet.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What you need:\n",
    "- A **Groq API key** → free at [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)\n",
    "- An **ngrok auth token** → free at [dashboard.ngrok.com](https://dashboard.ngrok.com)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Steps:\n",
    "1. Run **Cell 1** — installs Node.js, pnpm, and ngrok\n",
    "2. Run **Cell 2** — clones the project\n",
    "3. Run **Cell 3** — sets your API keys\n",
    "4. Run **Cell 4** — installs dependencies\n",
    "5. Run **Cell 5** — builds the frontend\n",
    "6. Run **Cell 6** — starts the backend and opens a public URL\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 1 — Install Node.js 20, npm, and ngrok"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Node.js 20 (LTS)\n",
    "!curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash -\n",
    "!apt-get install -y nodejs\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify\n",
    "!node --version\n",
    "!npm --version\n",
    "\n",
    "# Install ngrok\n",
    "!pip install pyngrok -q\n",
    "print('\\n✅ Node.js and ngrok installed')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 2 — Clone the project\n",
    "\n",
    "> If you already uploaded the project folder to Colab, skip this cell and set `PROJECT_DIR` to your folder path."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Option A: Clone from GitHub (replace with your repo URL) ──\n",
    "REPO_URL = \"https://github.com/Arjun-115/CoBug-ai-learning-platform.git\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Option B: If you uploaded a zip, unzip it instead ──\n",
    "# !unzip /content/ai-learning-platform.zip -d /content/\n",
    "\n",
    "!git clone {REPO_URL} /content/ai-learning-platform\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_DIR = \"/content/ai-learning-platform\"\n",
    "os.chdir(PROJECT_DIR)\n",
    "print(f'\\n✅ Project at: {PROJECT_DIR}')\n",
    "!ls"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 3 — Set your API keys\n",
    "\n",
    "**Replace the placeholder values below with your real keys.**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Groq key: [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com) → API Keys → Create\n",
    "- GitHub token (optional): [github.com/settings/tokens](https://github.com/settings/tokens)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── PASTE YOUR KEYS HERE ──\n",
    "GROQ_API_KEY    = \"gsk_your_groq_key_here\"       # Required\n",
    "GITHUB_TOKEN    = \"\"                              # Optional\n",
    "NGROK_AUTH_TOKEN = \"your_ngrok_auth_token_here\"  # Required for public URL\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write backend .env file\n",
    "env_content = f\"\"\"GROQ_API_KEY={GROQ_API_KEY}\n",
    "GITHUB_TOKEN={GITHUB_TOKEN}\n",
    "PORT=5000\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(\"/content/ai-learning-platform/backend/.env\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(env_content)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ backend/.env written\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set ngrok auth token\n",
    "from pyngrok import ngrok\n",
    "ngrok.set_auth_token(NGROK_AUTH_TOKEN)\n",
    "print(\"✅ ngrok auth token set\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4 — Install dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Installing backend dependencies...\")\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "    [\"npm\", \"install\"],\n",
    "    cwd=\"/content/ai-learning-platform/backend\",\n",
    "    capture_output=True, text=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(result.stdout[-500:] if result.stdout else \"\")\n",
    "if result.returncode != 0:\n",
    "    print(\"ERROR:\", result.stderr[-500:])\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Backend dependencies installed\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nInstalling frontend dependencies...\")\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "    [\"npm\", \"install\"],\n",
    "    cwd=\"/content/ai-learning-platform/frontend\",\n",
    "    capture_output=True, text=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(result.stdout[-500:] if result.stdout else \"\")\n",
    "if result.returncode != 0:\n",
    "    print(\"ERROR:\", result.stderr[-500:])\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Frontend dependencies installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 5 — Build the frontend\n",
    "\n",
    "This compiles React into static files that the backend will serve."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Building frontend (React + Vite)...\")\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "    [\"npm\", \"run\", \"build\"],\n",
    "    cwd=\"/content/ai-learning-platform/frontend\",\n",
    "    capture_output=True, text=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(result.stdout[-1000:] if result.stdout else \"\")\n",
    "if result.returncode != 0:\n",
    "    print(\"BUILD ERROR:\")\n",
    "    print(result.stderr[-1000:])\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Frontend built successfully\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Copy built files so backend can serve them\n",
    "import shutil, os\n",
    "src  = \"/content/ai-learning-platform/frontend/dist\"\n",
    "dest = \"/content/ai-learning-platform/backend/public\"\n",
    "if os.path.exists(dest):\n",
    "    shutil.rmtree(dest)\n",
    "shutil.copytree(src, dest)\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Built files copied to backend/public\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 5b — Patch backend to serve the frontend\n",
    "\n",
    "This adds static file serving to `server.js` so the backend serves the React app."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "server_patch = '''\n",
    "const path = require(\"path\");\n",
    "\n",
    "// Serve built React frontend from /public\n",
    "const PUBLIC_DIR = path.join(__dirname, \"public\");\n",
    "app.use(require(\"express\").static(PUBLIC_DIR));\n",
    "\n",
    "// All non-API routes → serve index.html (React Router support)\n",
    "app.get(\"*\", (req, res) => {\n",
    "  if (!req.path.startsWith(\"/api\")) {\n",
    "    res.sendFile(path.join(PUBLIC_DIR, \"index.html\"));\n",
    "  }\n",
    "});\n",
    "'''\n",
    "\n",
    "server_path = \"/content/ai-learning-platform/backend/server.js\"\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(server_path, \"r\") as f:\n",
    "    content = f.read()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Only patch if not already patched\n",
    "if \"serve built React\" not in content:\n",
    "    # Insert before initDb().then(...)\n",
    "    content = content.replace(\n",
    "        \"// Initialize DB first\",\n",
    "        server_patch + \"\\n// Initialize DB first\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    with open(server_path, \"w\") as f:\n",
    "        f.write(content)\n",
    "    print(\"✅ server.js patched to serve frontend\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ server.js already patched\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 6 — Start the server and get your public URL\n",
    "\n",
    "This starts the Node.js backend and creates a public ngrok tunnel.\n",
    "**Your app will be live at the URL printed below.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess, time, requests\n",
    "from pyngrok import ngrok\n",
    "\n",
    "# Kill any existing node processes\n",
    "subprocess.run([\"pkill\", \"-f\", \"node\"], capture_output=True)\n",
    "time.sleep(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Start the backend\n",
    "server = subprocess.Popen(\n",
    "    [\"node\", \"server.js\"],\n",
    "    cwd=\"/content/ai-learning-platform/backend\",\n",
    "    stdout=subprocess.PIPE,\n",
    "    stderr=subprocess.STDOUT\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Wait for it to start\n",
    "print(\"Starting server\", end=\"\")\n",
    "for _ in range(15):\n",
    "    time.sleep(1)\n",
    "    print(\".\", end=\"\", flush=True)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        r = requests.get(\"http://localhost:5000/\", timeout=2)\n",
    "        if r.status_code == 200:\n",
    "            print(\" ready!\")\n",
    "            break\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\" timeout — check logs below\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print server startup logs\n",
    "import os, fcntl\n",
    "fd = server.stdout.fileno()\n",
    "fl = fcntl.fcntl(fd, fcntl.F_GETFL)\n",
    "fcntl.fcntl(fd, fcntl.F_SETFL, fl | os.O_NONBLOCK)\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    logs = server.stdout.read()\n",
    "    if logs: print(logs.decode())\n",
    "except:\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "# Open ngrok tunnel\n",
    "public_url = ngrok.connect(5000)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n",
    "print(f\"🌐  CoBug AI Learning Platform is LIVE at:\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\n    {public_url}\\n\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*50)\n",
    "print(\"\\nOpen the URL above in any browser.\")\n",
    "print(\"The tunnel stays active as long as this cell is running.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 7 — View server logs (optional)\n",
    "\n",
    "Run this any time to see what the backend is doing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Read recent server output\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    logs = server.stdout.read()\n",
    "    print(logs.decode() if logs else \"No new logs\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Could not read logs: {e}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 8 — Stop the server (cleanup)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyngrok import ngrok\n",
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "ngrok.kill()\n",
    "subprocess.run([\"pkill\", \"-f\", \"node\"], capture_output=True)\n",
    "print(\"✅ Server and tunnel stopped\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Troubleshooting\n",
    "\n",
    "**`ngrok.connect` fails** → Make sure you set your ngrok auth token in Cell 3. Get one free at [dashboard.ngrok.com](https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken).\n",
    "\n",
    "**AI returns errors** → Check your Groq API key in Cell 3. Make sure it starts with `gsk_`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Build fails** → Re-run Cell 1 to reinstall Node.js, then retry Cell 4 and 5.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Page shows blank** → Re-run Cell 5b to make sure the backend is patched to serve the frontend.\n",
    "\n",
    "**GitHub repo analysis fails** → Public repos work without a token. For private repos, add a GitHub token in Cell 3.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "*CoBug AI Learning Platform — built with React, Node.js, and Groq*"
   ]
  }
 ]
}"
